dasan.name: dasan

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

dasan.description: The Structure of Management Information for the Dasan enterprise.

dasanEvents.name: dasanEvents
dasanEvents.description: dasanEvents is the root OBJECT IDENTIFIER of EVENTS(or TRAPS). Each EVENT(TRAP) is defined in Each Product MIB file.

dasanProducts.name: dasanProducts
dasanProducts.description: dasanProducts is the root OBJECT IDENTIFIER from which sysObjectID values are assigned. Actual values are defined in DASAN-PRODUCTS-MIB.

local.name: local
local.description: Subtree beneath which pre-10.2 MIBS were built.

temporary.name: temporary
temporary.description: Subtree beneath which pre-10.2 experiments were placed.

workgroup.name: workgroup
workgroup.description: subtree reserved for use by the Workgroup Business Unit

otherEnterprises.name: otherEnterprises
otherEnterprises.description: otherEnterprises provides a root object identifier from which mibs produced by other companies may be placed. mibs produced by other enterprises are typicially implemented with the object identifiers as defined in the mib, but if the mib is deemed to be uncontrolled, we may reroot the mib at this subtree in order to have a controlled version.

dasanAgentCapability.name: dasanAgentCapability
dasanAgentCapability.description: dasanAgentCapability provides a root object identifier from which AGENT-CAPABILITIES values may be assigned.

dasanConfig.name: dasanConfig
dasanConfig.description: dasanConfig is the main subtree for configuration mibs.

dasanMgmt.name: dasanMgmt
dasanMgmt.description: dasanMgmt is the main subtree for new mib development.

dasanExperiment.name: dasanExperiment
dasanExperiment.description: dasanExperiment provides a root object identifier from which experimental mibs may be temporarily based. mibs are typicially based here if they fall in one of two categories 1) are IETF work-in-process mibs which have not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the IANA. 2) are dasan work-in-process which has not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the dasan assigned number authority, typicially because the mib is not ready for deployment. NOTE WELL: support for mibs in the dasanExperiment subtree will be deleted when a permanent object identifier assignment is made.

dasanAdmin.name: dasanAdmin
dasanAdmin.description: dasanAdmin is reserved for administratively assigned OBJECT IDENTIFIERS, i.e. those not associated with MIB objects

dasanModules.name: dasanModules
dasanModules.description: dasanModules provides a root object identifier from which MODULE-IDENTITY values may be assigned.

lightstream.name: lightstream
lightstream.description: subtree reserved for use by Lightstream

dasanworks.name: dasanworks
dasanworks.description: dasanworks provides a root object identifier beneath which mibs applicable to the dasanWorks family of network management products are defined.

newport.name: newport
newport.description: subtree reserved for use by the former Newport Systems Solutions, now a portion of the Access Business Unit.

dasanPartnerProducts.name: dasanPartnerProducts
dasanPartnerProducts.description: dasanPartnerProducts is the root OBJECT IDENTIFIER from which partner sysObjectID values may be assigned. Such sysObjectID values are composed of the dasanPartnerProducts prefix, followed by a single identifier that is unique for each partner, followed by the value of sysObjectID of the dasan product from which partner product is derived. Note that the chassisPartner MIB object defines the value of the identifier assigned to each partner.

dasanPolicy.name: dasanPolicy
dasanPolicy.description: dasanPolicy is the root of the dasan-assigned OID subtree for use with Policy Management.
